portal.personalDetailsHeader:
This information is applicable to members of the Scout Association between the ages of 14 and 24, who are participating in the Duke of Edinburgh programme under the South East Explorer Expeditions programme run by South East Scotland Region(www.sesscouts.org.uk). The information will be stored in this online membership system (OSM) for the duration of the young person’s time with the Scout Association. These details can be accessed through OSM by adult volunteers with Duke of Edinburgh responsibilities, and the Region and District volunteers responsible for managing and running the programme. 
We use this information to communicate with you and to carry out our obligations as leaders in the Scout Association. In some cases this data will be Sensitive Personal Data, which we request to allow us to provide appropriate care for young people whilst under our supervision.
Please ensure all the details are filled in and up to date. 


If there is NO info that you need to have added - please type NONE or N/A in the text box.
